HEADWORD: Interposit
<hw>In`ter*pos"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>interpositus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>interponere</ets>. See
<er>Interposition</er>.]</ety> <def>An intermediate depot or station
between one commercial city or country and another.</def>
<rj><au>Mitford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

